  "Permission from residents to build a polluting facility in their neighborhood": "",
  "A court-approved settlement between the government and a polluter that requires specific cleanup actions and compliance measures": "",
  "An agreement between two companies to share pollution control costs": "",
  "A consent decree is a legally binding agreement approved by a court that resolves an environmental enforcement action. It typically requires the polluter to take specific remedial actions, pay penalties, and meet compliance milestones under judicial oversight.": "",
  "What does the term 'command-and-control regulation' mean in pollution policy?": "",
  "Military control of pollution sources": "",
  "Industry self-regulation without government involvement": "",
  "A video game about managing pollution": "",
  "Government regulations that set specific emission limits and prescribe technologies or methods for compliance": "",
  "Command-and-control regulation directly mandates pollution limits and often specifies the methods or technologies to achieve them. While effective at setting clear standards, it is often less cost-efficient than market-based approaches like cap-and-trade.": "",
  "What is the meaning of 'total maximum daily load' (TMDL)?": "",
  "The maximum number of pollution permits issued per day": "",
  "The maximum amount of a pollutant that a water body can receive daily and still meet water quality standards": "",
  "The maximum amount of cargo a truck can carry per day": "",
  "The total weight of waste processed daily at a landfill": "",
  "A TMDL is a calculation of the maximum amount of a pollutant that a water body can receive from all sources (point and non-point) and still safely meet water quality standards. TMDLs are required under the Clean Water Act for impaired waters.": "",
  "What does 'adaptive management' mean in environmental policy?": "",
