  "The Chesapeake Bay watershed covers 64,000 square miles across six states and D.C. with 18 million residents. The diffuse nature of non-point source pollution from agriculture, urban areas, and atmospheric deposition requires coordinating policies across multiple jurisdictions.": "",
  "In Minamata, Japan, a chemical factory discharged mercury into the bay for decades starting in the 1930s. By the 1950s, thousands of residents who ate contaminated fish developed severe neurological damage, birth defects, and many died. What regulatory lesson did this tragedy teach the world?": "",
