  "The emission targets were weakened after industry lobbying based on established principles": "",
  "The cap-and-trade system gave companies flexibility to find the cheapest compliance methods. Many switched to low-sulfur coal (available more cheaply than expected) or installed scrubbers, while the trading mechanism directed reductions to where they were least expensive.": "",
  "Following the Volkswagen emissions scandal of 2015, where the company installed software to cheat on diesel emissions tests, regulators discovered that vehicles emitted up to 40 times the legal limit of NOx during normal driving. What broader lesson does this case study provide about pollution control?": "",
  "Diesel vehicles should not be subject to emissions testing": "",
