  "Laboratory testing is always an accurate reflection of real-world emissions": "",
  "The Volkswagen scandal revealed that pollution standards are only effective when coupled with independent real-world testing and meaningful enforcement. VW's $30+ billion in fines and settlements demonstrates the cost of regulatory deception and the importance of verification.": "",
  "The Thames River in London was declared 'biologically dead' in 1957 due to centuries of sewage and industrial pollution. By 2021, over 115 species of fish had returned to the river. What combination of actions enabled this remarkable recovery?": "",
