  "Chemical treatments were added to the river to neutralize pollution": "",
  "The Thames recovery required billions of pounds invested in modern sewage treatment plants, strict regulation of industrial discharges, deindustrialization of the riverbanks, and decades of sustained commitment, demonstrating that even severely polluted waterways can recover with sufficient investment and regulation.": "",
  "Beijing's air quality was notoriously poor, with PM2.5 levels regularly exceeding 300 micrograms per cubic meter. Between 2013 and 2020, China invested heavily in pollution control measures and PM2.5 levels dropped by approximately 40%. Which specific policies were most impactful?": "",
