  "The Great Lakes Water Quality Agreement between the United States and Canada, first signed in 1972, targeted phosphorus pollution that was causing massive algal blooms in Lake Erie. By the 1990s, phosphorus levels had dropped significantly and Lake Erie's ecosystem improved. However, harmful algal blooms returned in the 2010s. What caused the resurgence?": "",
