  "While point source phosphorus from sewage treatment plants was successfully controlled, non-point source agricultural runoff containing dissolved reactive phosphorus (more biologically available) increased due to fertilizer practices, tile drainage, and warmer temperatures from climate change.": "",
  "The European Union's REACH regulation (Registration, Evaluation, Authorisation and Restriction of Chemicals) requires companies to prove that chemicals are safe before they can be sold, unlike the U.S. approach which generally requires regulators to prove chemicals are harmful. What fundamental policy difference does this represent?": "",
