  "REACH places the burden of proof on manufacturers (precautionary approach), while the U.S. traditionally places it on regulators (risk-based approach)": "",
  "The U.S. has stricter chemical regulations than the EU when applying fundamental principles": "",
  "REACH embodies the precautionary principle by requiring chemical manufacturers to demonstrate safety before market access. The U.S. approach under TSCA historically allowed chemicals to be used until regulators could prove harm, often after widespread exposure had already occurred.": "",
  "India's Ganges River is considered sacred by Hindus but is one of the most polluted rivers in the world, receiving untreated sewage from hundreds of cities and industrial waste from thousands of factories along its 1,500-mile length. Despite multiple cleanup campaigns costing billions of dollars, significant pollution persists. What is the primary obstacle to cleaning the Ganges?": "",
