  "Over 500 million people live in the Ganges basin, and most cities along the river lack adequate sewage treatment. Building sufficient infrastructure for such a massive population while simultaneously enforcing industrial regulations across thousands of facilities presents an enormous challenge.": "",
  "After decades of decline, the peregrine falcon population in the United States recovered from fewer than 40 breeding pairs in the 1970s to over 3,000 pairs by 2020, allowing it to be removed from the Endangered Species List. This success story involved banning DDT, captive breeding, and habitat protection. An ecologist argues that this case provides a template for other pollution-related species recovery efforts. What key principle does this case study demonstrate?": "",
